  "text": "Functions with memory. In some keystream generators, the filtering function is replaced by a finite automaton with some memory bits. An example is the E 0 keystream generator used in the Bluetooth wireless LAN system, which uses a combining function with 4 inputs and 4 memory bits. However, (fast) algebraic attacks [CITATION_1] can still be applied on such systems. Armknecht and Krause proved that, for any filtering function of n variables with M memory bits, there always exists a relation of degree at most",
